docs.abstract: Nyjah Huston’s signature dreadlocks are stored in a box now, an artifact of his early fame. The effects of his complicated upbringing have not been so easy to cut off.
docs.snippet: Nyjah Huston’s signature dreadlocks are stored in a box now, an artifact of his early fame. The effects of his complicated upbringing have not been so easy to cut off.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAGUNA BEACH, Calif. — Nyjah Huston was driving his Mercedes coupe well past the speed limit between his $3 million house overlooking the Pacific Ocean and his private indoor skatepark where he was training for the Olympics.

docs.abstract: In comments still rippling through the network, the reporter Rachel Nichols, who is white, said Maria Taylor, who is Black, earned the job to host 2020 N.B.A. finals coverage because ESPN was “feeling pressure” on diversity.
docs.snippet: In comments still rippling through the network, the reporter Rachel Nichols, who is white, said Maria Taylor, who is Black, earned the job to host 2020 N.B.A. finals coverage because ESPN was “feeling pressure” on diversity.
docs.lead_paragraph: As the N.B.A. playoffs started in May, the stars of ESPN’s marquee basketball show, “NBA Countdown,” discussed whether they would refuse to appear on it.

headline.main: A Disparaging Video Prompts Explosive Fallout Within ESPN
headline.print_headline: A Leaked Video Inflames The Racial Turmoil at ESPN

docs.abstract: Democrats and Republicans are already jockeying for a crucial voting bloc that soured on Donald Trump, tilted to Joe Biden and now holds the key to the second half of the president’s term.
docs.snippet: Democrats and Republicans are already jockeying for a crucial voting bloc that soured on Donald Trump, tilted to Joe Biden and now holds the key to the second half of the president’s term.
docs.lead_paragraph: PAPILLION, Neb. — Pursuing a bipartisan infrastructure deal and trumpeting a revived economy and progress against the pandemic, President Biden is trying to persuade the nation that Democrats are the party that gets things done. His message is aimed at holding on to a set of voters in next year’s midterms who could determine the fate of his agenda: suburbanites who abandoned former President Donald Trump in droves.

headline.main: The Big Question of the 2022 Midterms: How Will the Suburbs Swing?
headline.print_headline: Biden’s Agenda Rests on Appeal In the Suburbs

docs.abstract: The league made a 10-year commitment to the Players Alliance that includes $10 million a year, plus an additional $5 million in matching contributions.
docs.snippet: The league made a 10-year commitment to the Players Alliance that includes $10 million a year, plus an additional $5 million in matching contributions.
docs.lead_paragraph: Major League Baseball announced on Monday that it would donate up to $150 million to the Players Alliance, a nonprofit formed last summer by more than 100 Black current and former players in the wake of George Floyd’s death. The donation is aimed at helping build Black participation in the sport.

headline.main: M.L.B. Pledges Millions to Build Black Participation

docs.abstract: A politically active company just waded into one of the most fraught issues in the world, and the reaction was immediate.
docs.snippet: A politically active company just waded into one of the most fraught issues in the world, and the reaction was immediate.
docs.lead_paragraph: Ben & Jerry’s, the ice cream purveyor famous for taking stands on hot-button social issues, announced Monday that it was ending sales in the Israeli-occupied territories — plunging itself into one of the most contentious debates on the international stage.

headline.main: Ben & Jerry’s to Stop Selling Ice Cream in Israeli-Occupied Territories

docs.abstract: Mr. Moses developed a reputation for extraordinary calm in the face of violence as he helped to register thousands of voters and trained a generation of activists in Mississippi in the early 1960s.
docs.snippet: Mr. Moses developed a reputation for extraordinary calm in the face of violence as he helped to register thousands of voters and trained a generation of activists in Mississippi in the early 1960s.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bob Moses, a soft-spoken pioneer of the civil rights movement who faced relentless intimidation and brutal violence to register Black voters in Mississippi in the 1960s, and who later started a national organization devoted to teaching math as a means to a more equal society, died on Sunday at his home in Hollywood, Fla. He was 86.

headline.main: Bob Moses, Crusader for Civil Rights and Math Education, Dies at 86
headline.print_headline: Bob Moses, a Quiet and Relentless Crusader for Civil Rights, Dies at 86

docs.abstract: Prosecutors did not charge the suspect, Fi Duong, with crimes of violence but accused him of planning to use Molotov cocktails and of conducting surveillance at the Capitol after Jan. 6.
docs.snippet: Prosecutors did not charge the suspect, Fi Duong, with crimes of violence but accused him of planning to use Molotov cocktails and of conducting surveillance at the Capitol after Jan. 6.
docs.lead_paragraph: In mid-June, a self-described Virginia militiaman drove with a new acquaintance from his home in Alexandria to a former prison in the nearby town of Lorton, about 15 miles away. His mission was a secret one, prosecutors say: He was scouting a location where he could test a batch of Molotov cocktails he was planning to make.

headline.main: Self-Described Virginia Militiaman Is Arrested in Capitol Breach
headline.print_headline: Undercover F.B.I. Operation Leads to Criminal Charges For a Marine Corps Veteran

docs.abstract: After facing a torrent of racist abuse online, Bukayo Saka said he didn’t want anyone to deal with such “hateful and hurtful messages.”
docs.snippet: After facing a torrent of racist abuse online, Bukayo Saka said he didn’t want anyone to deal with such “hateful and hurtful messages.”
docs.lead_paragraph: After Bukayo Saka missed a penalty kick for England’s national team on Sunday in the final of the European soccer championship, he and several teammates were overwhelmed by a wave of racist abuse.

headline.main: English Soccer Player Urges Facebook and Twitter to Crack Down on Abuse
headline.print_headline: Player Urges Social Media To Take Stand Against Abuse
